n, we find evidence that the covering factor of the\nobscuring material decreases with $L_{X}$ for all redshifts, consistent with\nthe receding torus model, and that this factor increases with redshift,\nconsistent with an increase in the obscured fraction towards higher redshifts.\nWe make $N_{H}$, $\\Gamma$ (with uncertainties), observed X-ray fluxes and\nintrinsic $L_{X}$ for all sources analysed in this work publicly available in\nan online catalogue.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 Jun 2014 20:00:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-22"}
